{
  "stem": "27509.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a pogrom, if you know, and the interregnum between the Polish people leaving and the Lithuanian people just arriving.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the minute they spotted me, they recognized that I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They threw me to the floor, and they were kicking me with their-- with their feet and hurting me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By the time-- by the time a policeman came up to, like, have a look at the situation, my face was like that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I took refuge in one of the houses there, and I didn't dare come out for hours, because-- until the street emptied out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was my personal experience, and it took me a couple of-- a couple of months before the swelling and the blue, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] under my eyes, has disappeared sufficiently to be able not to have to wear glasses.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was [? '94. ?]",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I lived with a family of Hasidic Jews, also in the heart of town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was a curious insight into life there, in the sense that, of course, the Warsaw Jew was, by and large, Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But their children were already, if not assimilated, at least certainly not Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And whilst-- when Father and Mother want to talk between themselves without their children understand what-- they used to talk Yiddish to one another.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was already a foreign language for their own children, although they were Hasidic themselves, to such an extent the gap between just one generation has been-- I didn't stay long.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't [INAUDIBLE] also, because, again, if I had to submit to pressures at secondary school in year 11 and 12, how much more it was the case afterwards.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And after awhile, I decided, well, I've had a taste of that.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
